The paper presents a developmental framework for a robot to optimize hyper-parameters of black-box modules using long-term memory and reasoning mechanisms. The paper involves topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves autonomous learning, optimization, and reasoning. The paper also involves topics related to robotics (cs.RO) as it involves the use of a robotic arm for experimentation. The paper also involves topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of Bayesian optimization for hyper-parameter tuning. The paper also involves topics related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves the use of visual similarity for transfer learning. Finally, the paper also involves topics related to control systems (cs.SY) as it involves the optimization of control parameters for a robotic arm.
